Working with tensors¶

Defining a tensor/constant¶

In [5]:

tensor
Out[5]:
<tf.Tensor: shape=(2, 2), dtype=int32, numpy=
array([[1, 2],
       [4, 8]])>

Out[6]:

In [7]:

Out[7]:

       [4, 8]])

Defining constants from numpy arrays¶

In [8]:

Out[8]:

       [32.2,  1. ]])

array([[12. , 44. ],

Building machine learning models¶

  • Keras provides high level APIs which are easier and more intuitive to build machine learning models.
  • In Keras, we assemble layers to build models.
  • A model is typically a graph of layers which consist of different types of layer and constructor parameters.
  • These constructor parameters include number of neurons in the layer, activation function, regularization,

In [22]:
model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
    # Add a densely-connected layer with 6 units to the model
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(6, activation = 'linear', input_shape = [8]),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(6, activation = 'relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(4, activation = 'softmax')
])
In [23]:
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])
model.summary()
